title: Despite heavy secrecy, portraits emerging of those detained at LAX under Trump order
text: As of Sunday night, U.S. Customs and Border Protection had processed all cases of individuals initially affected by Trump's order at airports around the nation, according to Gillian Christensen, acting spokeswoman for the Department of Homeland Security. Christensen, however, said in an email that she was unsure whether additional travelers were being processed on Monday.
